Coconut crusted French toast anyone? Recipe below.⬇️ Cuban bread, bright lime zest, warm spices, and what every weekend needs, rum, make this a total taste of the tropics.

Have an amazing weekend everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today!

8 Slices Cuban bread
2 eggs
1 egg yolk
1/2 cup half and half or whole milk
1/8 cup dark rum
2 tbsp brown sugar
1 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp allspice 
1/4 tsp nutmeg 
1 tbsp lime zest
Pinch of kosher salt
1/2 cup unsweetened coconut flakes
1/4 panko breadcrumbs 
2 tbsp unsalted butter 

Add the eggs, egg yolk, sugar, and spices to a bowl and whisk to combine. Add the milk, rum, and zest and continue to whisk until combined.

In a separate bowl mix together the coconut and panko.

Dip the bread into the custard mixture, allowing it to soak through. Dip both sides of the bread into the coconut mixture, slightly pressing it in. Continue with the remaining bread.

Heat a griddle or skillet on medium heat and melt the butter. Add the bread to the hot skillet and let the first side cook for 4-5 minutes or until golden brown. Flip and cook another 4-5 minutes.

Garnish with extra toasted coconut if desired.

#frenchtoast #brunchtime #coconutlover #cubanbread

Where are my tomato lovers at? ⬇️Recipe below for green bean and tomato salad.🍅 Red wine vinegar, two types of mustard, shallots, and honey make the dressing for this easy salad bright and refreshing. You can dress it up with feta or blue cheese, toss in artichokes, or serve it up just as is. 

Have an amazing day everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today.

12 oz green beans, trimmed
1 1/2 cups grape or cherry tomatoes halved
1 sweet onion, sliced
1 shallot finely minced
1 tsp honey
2 tbsp red wine vinegar 
1 tbsp water
1/2 tbsp Dijon mustard 
1/2 tbsp whole grain mustard 
1/4 cup olive oil
1 tbsp chives, snipped
1 tbsp dill, chopped
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp freshly cracked black pepper
Optional add ins: feta, blue cheese, olives, marinated artichoke hearts, shaved Parmigiano-Reggiano, basil instead of dill 

Bring a pot of water to a boil and add 1 tbsp salt. Add the green beans and blanch for 3-5 minutes until bright green and tender-crisp. Drain and transfer to a bowl of salted ice water. Once cool drain. 

Add the shallots to a bowl along with vinegar, water, and honey. Stir until honey is dissolved. Let sit for at least 5 minutes.

Add both mustards and whisk to combine. While whisking stream in the olive oil, continuing to whisk until emulsified.

Add the green beans, onions, tomatoes, herbs, salt, pepper, and any add-ins. Gently fold until fully coated. Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.

Can be served room temperature or chilled. For less Al dente green beans skip shocking in the salted iced water bath and immediately drain. They will continue to cook as they cool. For a tangier dressing omit the water.
#tomatolover #summersalad #greenbeansalad #summerveggies #saladrecipe #saladlover #orlandofoodie

Grilled brie with slumped tomatoes, because I love cheese and tomatoes.❤️🍅 This is a quick and easy appetizer that you can totally customize to what you like and what you have on hand. Hate olives? Leave them out. Not a fan of spice? Skip the crushed red pepper flakes. Method below. This was grilled on the @aspirebyhestan.

💙Stick your wheel of brie in the freezer for 10-15 minutes. It makes it easier to remove the top rind.
💙 Toss together halved grape tomatoes, Castelvetrano olives, and pepperoncini with thinly sliced garlic, crushed red pepper flakes, fresh thyme, lemon zest, olive oil, and a couple tbsp of dry white wine.
💙 Remove the top of the rind from the brie and place in the center of a small cast iron. Nestle the tomato mixture around the brie. Season the brie with pepper, a pinch of salt, and fresh thyme.
💙 Grill indirect for 10-15 minutes until the brie is melted and the tomatoes have begin to slump.
💙 Drizzle with balsamic glaze and serve with crusty bread.

Seared scallops, is there anything better? These U 10/20 day boat scallops from @lobsteranywhere are truly the ultimate bite of the sea. They don’t need a lot to shine.

🌊 Remove the side muscle from your scallops. Don’t skip this quick step.
🌊 Pat them dry.
🌊 Lightly season. I used fine sea salt and a little pepper for these, and don’t season ahead of time. It draws out moisture.
🌊 Get your pan or griddle hot. You want it almost smoking.
🌊 Let your scallops cook for 2 minutes on the first side. I start mine in oil and add butter when I flip. If they don’t easily release from the pan, give them a second.
🌊 Cook the second side another 2 minutes. They should still have a little spring when you touch them. Remove from the pan.
🌊 I deglaze with a splash of white wine and garnish with a little minced parsley and lemon zest.

Have an amazing day everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today! And eat more seafood!🦞

Mini butter poached lobster rolls, you know you want one! ⬇️Method below.⬇️ These mini lobster roll kits from @lobsteranywhere not only come with the sweetest claw, knuckle, and tail meat begging to be eaten straight from the pan but also everything you need to make them including the rolls and sweet Maine sea salt butter. These are perfect for a party while also just turning a weeknight into an event! These were cooked on my @pkgrills AF300.

Have an amazing weekend everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today. And eat more seafood!🦞

🦞 Bring 2-4 tbsp of water to a boil. I also add 1 finely diced shallot.
🦞 Once boiling lower heat or move to indirect heat if on the grill. 
🦞 Add a couple cubes of cold butter at a time whisking continuously. You can freeze it for a few if you like. Add 1 cup of butter total.
🦞 Once emulsified add your lobster. Baste it occasionally with the warm butter. If your butter starts to break,briefly remove from the heat while gently stirring.
🦞 Allow the lobster to cook for 5-8 minutes until it is opaque, brighter in color, and firm but still has a spring. Aim for between 135-140 degrees.
🦞 Toss in fresh herbs. I used dill, chives, and flat leaf parsley, along with some lemon zest.
🦞 Don’t forget to toast those brioche rolls!

Honey-Chipotle butterflied shrimp.🦐Recipe below.⬇️ These 8/12 count super colossal shrimp from @lobsteranywhere were sweet and succulent. Butterflying them allowed for a faster cooking time, more surface area for seasoning, and because of their size kept them tender without overcooking. They were grilled on the @pkgrills 300AF with @honeytruckco Bourbon Honey bringing the right amount of sweet to balance the heat. Have an amazing weekend everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today. And eat more seafood!

1 lbs 8-12 count shrimp, peeled & deveined, can also use 16/20 count
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp granulated garlic
1/4 tsp paprika
1/4 tsp coriander 
1/8 tsp chipotle powder
8 tbsp unsalted butter 
1-2 chipotle peppers, finely chopped
2 tbsp honey
2 garlic cloves grated
2 tsp lime zest
1 tsp lime juice
1/8 cup cilantro finely chopped

🦐 Butterfly shrimp. Pat both sides dry.
🦐 Add you spices to a small bowl and mix to combine. Sprinkle seasoning over both sides of the shrimp.
🦐 Prepare your grill for direct grilling. Make sure your charcoal is in an even layer.
🦐 Add the butter, chipotles, honey, and garlic to a grill safe pot and place on the grill. Stir to melt. Add the lime juice and zest and cilantro and stir to combine. Place the pot on the indirect side to keep it warm. You will want to remove about 1/4 cup for basting.
🦐 Place the butterflied shrimp over direct heat. Allow the first side to grill for 2 minutes. The tails will begin to turn pink and the flesh opaque.
🦐 Flip them and give them a baste with the reserved butter. If they seem to be cooking too quickly move them to indirect heat.
🦐 Cook them for another 2 minutes or until their internal temperature is 120 degrees. They will be slightly curled.
🦐 Remove from the heat and serve with reserved butter.
🦐 This butter is also delicious on lobster!🦞
#grilledshrimp #grilledseafood #seafoodie #seafoodlover #shrimplover

Happy #nationalmojitoday! There is just something about a mojito that always makes me feel like I’m on vacation and this blueberry-cherry mojito is one of my favorites. Recipe below.⬇️ Have an amazing day everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today.

Cherry-mint simple syrup 
1 cup water
1 cup sugar
1 1/2 cups cherries, pitted and halved
3-4 sprigs of mint
Add all of the ingredients to a small saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar. Remove from heat and allow to steep for 30 minutes. Strain out the cherries and mint. Chill completely before making cocktails.

Red, white, and blue(berry) mojitos
1/2 cup blueberries
6 mint leaves, torn
4 oz white rum
1 lime, halved 
2-4 tbsp cherry-mint simple syrup 
Club soda
Ice cubes
Garnish: cherries, blueberries, mint 
Divide the blueberries and mint between two cocktail glasses. Using a muddler, or the back of a wooden spoon, crush the blueberries and mint. Add 2 oz rum to each cocktail along with the juice of 1/2 lime. Depending how sweet you like your cocktail add 1-2 tbsp of simple syrup to each glass. Stir. Fill the glasses with ice, top with club soda, and garnish. I like to freeze blueberries to add as ice cubes. Cheers!

#mojitotime #cocktailrecipe #rumdrinks #rumcocktails #cocktailtime

1 lbs lobster cooked meat, chopped*
16 oz cavatappi, or pasta of choice
3 tbsp unsalted butter
1 large shallot, minced
2 garlic cloves, minced
4 1/2 tbsp flour
1/4 cup Prosecco or dry white wine, room temperature 
2 3/4 cups whole milk
1 tsp mustard powder
3/4 tsp freshly cracked black pepper 
1/4 tsp cayenne 
Salt to taste
8 oz fontina, shredded, room temp
8 oz mascarpone cheese, room temp
1/4 cup Parmigiano-Reggiano, grated, room temp
1/2 tbsp lemon zest
Heat milk in a small saucepan on low heat.  Cook pasta in salted water according to package directions to al dente. Drain. Heat a large pot or skillet over medium heat. Melt butter. Add your garlic and shallots and season with a pinch of salt. Sauté for 2-3 minutes until fragrant and the shallots are translucent. Sprinkle flour over the top. Continually stir until butter is absorbed and the flour begins to smell nutty. Slowly add in Prosecco or wine while stirring. Cook for 1-2 minutes. 1/2 cup at a time slowly add warm milk, whisking continually and waiting to add the next 1/2 until incorporated. Once all of the milk has been added stir in seasonings. Hold off adding additional salt until after cheeses are melted. Continue to stir until sauce has thickened. It should coat the back of a spoon and hug it. Add your mascarpone cheese and stir to incorporate. Add the fontina and parm, stirring to melt and combine. Add drained pasta, stirring to completely coat the pasta. Fold in lobster and lemon zest. Allow to heat through. If using top with toasted panko. Buon appetito! #cheeseplease #macandcheese #cheeselover #seafoodie #seafoodlover #cheesyfood

Happy #nationalicecreamday! Tropical banana’s Foster made on the @aspirebyhestan. Recipe below. @kellyshomemadeicecream toasted coconut ice cream took this over the top! Have an amazing day everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness today.

4 bananas, firm, cut into 1” halves
4 tbsp salted butter
3/4 cup brown sugar
¼ tsp cinnamon
¼ cup orange juice
¼ dark rum
1 tbsp orange zest
½ cup coconut flakes
½ cup unsalted macadamia nuts, chopped
Coconut or vanilla ice cream for serving
Heat grill to 350-400 degrees. Place a grill safe skillet over direct heat and allow it to heat through.
Add coconut flakes and macadamia nuts. Continually stir them until they are lightly toasted and golden, 3-4 minutes. Set aside.
Return the pan to the grill. Melt the butter, brown sugar, and cinnamon, stirring until the sugar is slightly dissolved. It will be a little lumpy.
Add the orange juice and continue to stir until it is bubbly.
Place the bananas into the skillet, cut side down. Allow them to cook for 2 minutes.
Remove the skillet from the heat and pour in the rum. Carefully use a lighter to flambe the rum. Allow it to cook until the flames burn off.
Stir in the orange zest.
To serve, scoop ice cream into individual bowls. Top with the bananas and caramel sauce. Sprinkle the toasted coconut and macadamias over the top.

Looking for the perfect make ahead dish to serve for New Years brunch? This mushroom & kale strata is it. Recipe below. Packed full of savory flavors this will satisfy vegetarians and meat lovers alive. But you can totally add in cooked bacon or sausage if desired. Make sure to use a baguette that is a day or two old for the best results. This can be assembled the night before and refrigerated until baked the next morning. Have an incredible day everyone! Go out and spread a little positivity and kindness!

1 day old loaf Italian, French, or sourdough cut into 1” cubes
2 tbsp olive oil divided 
16 oz cremini mushrooms quartered
1 sweet onion diced
2 garlic cloves minced
1 bunch Tuscan kale,  ribs removed, chopped
1 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
1/2 tsp fresh black pepper
1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper flakes, optional 
2 teaspoons fresh thyme, chopped
1/4 tsp dry white wine, optional 
1 bunch green onions chopped
8 eggs
2 cups whole milk
1 cup heavy cream
1 tbsp Dijon mustard 
8 ounces Gruyere, Swiss, or sharp white cheddar grated
1/4 cup parmesan cheese grated

Heat a large skillet over medium and add a tbsp of oil. Add the mushrooms and allow them to cook until beginning to brown. Add the onion, thyme, garlic, 1/2 tsp salt, and red pepper flakes. Let cook for another 2-3 minutes until the onions are becoming translucent. Deglaze with white wine and let cook for 1 minute if using.

Next add the kale stirring until it has wilted. Turn off the heat and stir in the green onions. Let the mixture cool.

Add the eggs to a large bowl and use a whisk to break their yolks. Whisk to break them up. Add the milk, cream, Dijon, remaining salt, and pepper and whisk to completely combine. Fold in the shredded Gruyere, veggie mixture, and bread cubes.
Transfer the mixture to a buttered baking dish. You can allow this to refrigerate overnight. If baking immediately let it sit for 20 minutes to fully absorb the custard.

Just before baking sprinkle the Parmesan on top. Allow the strata to bake in a 350 degree oven or grill for 35-40 minutes until golden brown and puffy. If baking this on the grill let it bake indirect, rotating a couple of times during the process to bake evenly.

It might be cold outside but this winter citrus salad will make you feel like you’re in the sunshine. With an orange-honey vinaigrette with @spiceandtea orange infused olive oil and the citrusy pop of Florida Sunshine adding the perfect seasoning this salad is a true feast for the senses. Crunchy pistachios Persian cucumbers, creamy goat cheese and avocado, and that fun juicy burst of citrus in every bite, it will chase away the winter blues. Recipe below.🍋🍊

Winter Citrus Salad 
* 4 cups baby arugula
* 1 Blood orange, peeled and sliced
* 1 Cara Cara orange, peeled and sliced
* 1 Sumo mandarin orange, peeled and sliced
* 1 red grapefruit, peeled and sliced
* 1 avocado sliced
* ⅓ cup Persian or English cucumber sliced
* ¼ cup red onion shaved 
* ¼ cup goat cheese crumbled, optional
* ¼ cup salted roasted pistachios roughly chopped
* ¼ cup fresh basil or mint leaves torn
* Spice & Tea Florida Sunshine

Orange-Honey Vinaigrette
* 3 tablespoons Spice & Tea Olive Oil
* 1 tablespoon Spice & Tea Orange Olive Oil
* 2 tablespoons Cara Cara or Sumo orange juice
* 1 tablespoon champagne vinegar
* 2 teaspoons Spice & Tea Arbol Chile Honey
* 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard
* ⅛ teaspoon Spice & Tea Florida Sunshine

Directions
1. Add all of the ingredients to a mason jar and cover. Shake vigorously to emulsify. 
2. Arrange the arugula on a serving platter and drizzle a little of the dressing over the greens. Toss to combine. 
3. Arrange the citrus slices, avocado, cucumber, and onion over the greens. Top with the goat cheese, pistachios, and basil.  
4. Drizzle additional dressing over the top of the salad, reserving the remaining vinaigrette so guests can add additional. 
5. Season the salad with Florida Sunshine and enjoy!
